Package ch.nolix.core.invalidStateException

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ClosedStateException
    A closed state exception is an invalid state exception that is supposed to be thrown when an object is undesired closed.
    EmptyStateException
    An empty state exception is an invalid state exception that is supposed to be thrown when an object is undesired empty.
    InvalidStateException
    An invalid state exception is an exception that intended to be thrown when an object is in an invalid state.
    UnexistingAttributeException
    An unexisting attribute exception is an invalid state exception that is supposed to be thrown when an object has not an a desired attribute.
    UnremovableAttributeException
    An unremovable attribute exception is an invalid state exception that is intended to be thrown when an object cannot remove an undesired attribute.
    UnsupportedMethodException
    An unsupported method exception is an invalid state exception that is intended to be thrown when an object does not support a called method.
    UntimelyMethodException
    An untimely method exception is an invalid state exception that is intended to be thrown when an object is not in a state for a called method.
